    Farmer disease detection app

    A simple, farmer-friendly AI disease detection web app with 3 pages:Upload leaf image with big camera/upload button,Results page showing disease name, confidence score, and treatment in a clean card layout,Digital Twin page showing an embedded 3D plant model that changes color based on health status.Style it in green and earthy tones with large buttons and simple icons.”

    I'll create a farmer-friendly AI disease detection web app with a clean, earthy design and the three pages you requested.

    Version 1

    I've created a comprehensive farmer-friendly AI disease detection web app with all the features you requested:

    Key Features:

    Upload Page (Home)

    • Large, prominent camera and upload buttons
    • Visual feedback with image preview
    • Helpful photo tips for farmers
    • Clean, earthy green design

    Results Page

    • Disease detection results with confidence scores
    • Treatment and prevention recommendations
    • Clean card layout with severity indicators
    • Easy-to-read information for farmers

    Digital Twin Page

    • Interactive 3D plant model using React Three Fiber
    • Color-changing plant based on health status (green=healthy, yellow=diseased, red=critical)
    • Orbit controls for 360° viewing
    • Real-time health status panel

    Design Features:

    • Green & earthy color scheme throughout
    • Large, accessible buttons perfect for farm use
    • Simple icons from Lucide React
    • Responsive design works on mobile and desktop
    • Farmer-friendly language and clear instructions

    Technical Features:

    • File upload with camera capture support
    • Mock AI disease detection simulation
    • 3D visualization with Three.js/React Three Fiber
    • Session storage for data persistence
    • Smooth navigation between pages

    The app simulates real disease detection and provides practical treatment advice that farmers can easily understand and implement. The 3D digital twin provides an engaging visual representation of plant health status.

    change the name from Plant Health Detector to AgriVision

    Version 2

    Perfect! I've updated the app name from "Plant Health Detector" to "AgriVision" across all three pages. The new name gives it a more modern, tech-forward feel while still being farmer-friendly and clearly indicating its agricultural focus.

    make it similar to apple website and cool

    Version 3

    I've completely redesigned AgriVision with a sleek, Apple-inspired aesthetic! Here are the key improvements:

    Apple-Inspired Design Features:

    Visual Design

    • Dark theme with black backgrounds and white text
    • Glassmorphism effects with backdrop blur and transparency
    • Gradient accents throughout the interface
    • Rounded corners (rounded-3xl, rounded-full buttons)
    • Subtle borders with white/10 opacity
    • Premium typography with Apple system fonts

    Modern UI Elements

    • Fixed navigation header with backdrop blur
    • Large hero sections with gradient text effects
    • Smooth hover animations with scale transforms
    • Premium button styles with rounded-full design
    • Card-based layouts with subtle shadows and blur effects
    • Sophisticated color palette using opacity-based colors

    Enhanced User Experience

    • Smooth transitions on all interactive elements
    • Loading animations with custom spinners
    • Hover effects that scale elements
    • Professional spacing with generous padding
    • Clean typography hierarchy with proper font weights

    Cool Features

    • Gradient text effects for headings
    • Animated loading states
    • Interactive 3D model with better lighting
    • Status badges with color-coded health indicators
    • Feature cards with icon gradients
    • Pro tips section with amber accent colors

    The app now has that premium, sophisticated feel similar to Apple's website while maintaining its agricultural focus and farmer-friendly functionality. The dark theme with colorful accents creates a modern, tech-forward impression that would appeal to both tech-savvy farmers and agricultural professionals.
